{"updated_at": "2012-06-08T08:09:20Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2012-06-08T08:07:03Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/6196553", "id": 6196553, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/6324", "issue_id": 6324, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rajatvig/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/rajatvig", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rajatvig/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rajatvig/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rajatvig/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "ae8d8a8bd5baca4eb6e647e91aa11fb8", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rajatvig/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/rajatvig", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rajatvig/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/ae8d8a8bd5baca4eb6e647e91aa11fb8?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F56c6d19ee947025ec19f9eb9b283f368.png", "id": 63058, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rajatvig/events{/privacy}", "login": "rajatvig", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rajatvig/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rajatvig/followers"}, "body": "The backport fix has broken code on our end when using ActiveModel::Validations inside a Hashie::Dash.\n\nScenario\n\n```ruby\nclass A < Hashie::Dash\n  property :a, :default => \"b\"\nend\n\nA.new.to_s\n#<A a=\"b\">\nA.new.dup.keys\n[\"a\"]\n\nclass B < Hashie::Dash\n  include ActiveModel::Validations\n  property :a, :default => \"b\"\nend\n\nB.new.to_s\n#<B>\nB.new.dup.keys\n[]\n\n```\nThe fix is to call super at the end of initialized_dup.\nWe are using Ruby 1.9.3p194. The hashie gem is 1.x.", "_id": {"$oid": "52380b64bd3543c15100d004"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/6324#issuecomment-6196553"}
